DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Prolymphocyte Result Percentage Integer::1 Decimal Place Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 1 decimal place numeric laboratory percentage value measured, assigned or computed related to the assessment of prolymphocytes in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information relating to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for promyelocytes, a medium-sized round lymphocyte of B or T-cell lineage that is an intermediate cell between the lymphoblast and the small, mature lymphocyte.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: A medium-sized round lymphocyte of B or T-cell lineage with prominent nucleoli.  It is an intermediate cell between the lymphoblast and the small, mature lymphocyte.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: A medium-sized round lymphocyte of B or T-cell lineage with prominent nucleoli.  It is an intermediate cell between the lymphoblast and the small, mature lymphocyte.
